    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not melting, the needle is definitely fine. it's just like... these tiny little ripples and pulls right along the stitch line. i've tried adjusting the tension on both top and bottom but it's still happening. could it be something with the feed dogs or the way the fabric is being pulled through?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The small ripples and pulls could be due to the fabric's tendency to drag or slip through the presser foot, causing uneven tension and distortion. Check the feed dogs alignment and adjustment, making sure they're not eating into the fabric, which could be contributing to the puckering. You may also try lowering the presser foot pressure or using a walking foot or Teflon foot to help guide the fabric smoothly.",
